## Most recent state (May 13, 2026 — password reset bug fix + Supabase Pro)

**Customer Ashley Beine bug** — `/account/reset-password` was broken for all customers using the Forgot Password flow. The page only read `?token_hash=` from `req.query`, but Supabase recovery links redirect with `#access_token=jwt` in the URL hash fragment, which the server never sees. Anyone using Forgot Password landed on "This reset link is invalid or has expired" regardless of whether their link was actually expired. Fixed in commit `9f92d55` — the page now handles both flows (server-side POST for `?token_hash=` links, client-side JS that parses `#access_token=` and PUTs to /auth/v1/user for the hash-fragment flow, same pattern as `/set-password`). Ashley was sent a custom apology email + fresh 24-hour link via Resend (commit `5e8a07e`, removed in `89dfb8c`). Resend confirms delivered.

**Supabase upgrades (May 13 2026):**
- Plan upgraded from Free → **Pro** ($25/mo) at org level
- Email OTP expiry bumped to **86400s (24h)** — was 1h. Applies to welcome-email set-password links, forgot-password resets, and any other Supabase email-based OTP
- **Leaked-password protection** turned on (HaveIBeenPwned API check on signup + password change) — only available on Pro tier
- RLS enabled on `celebration_photos` and `recipe_photos` (Supabase Advisor flagged these as the only public-schema tables without RLS — backend uses service-role which bypasses RLS, so no policies needed)

