**⚠️ EAS iOS submit gotcha (May 6 2026):** The first two `eas submit --platform ios` attempts for v1.0.9 failed with Expo's generic "Something went wrong when submitting your app to Apple App Store Connect." — `error: null` and `logFiles: []` in the GraphQL submission record. Apple's status page was all green at the time. The third attempt (same build, no config changes, just re-running) succeeded immediately. Conclusion: EAS submit's worker pool occasionally fails transiently with no actionable error. **Don't debug; just retry up to 3x before investigating.**

**Landing v2 redesign — A/B test LIVE on / (commit `14a0c6c`, May 6 2026):**
- File: `src/views/marketing/landing-v2.ejs` (uses `.lo-` CSS prefix).
- `/` now serves v1 OR v2 via cookie-based 50/50 split (`pickLandingVariant` in `src/routes/book.js`).
- Cookie `lo_landing` (30-day expiry) keeps each visitor sticky to one variant.
- Bots/crawlers (Googlebot, Bingbot, facebookexternalhit, Twitterbot, etc.) always get v1 for SEO/canonical stability.
- Manual override: `?lov=v1` or `?lov=v2` (also sets the cookie).
