**Gift-giver landing + scheduled delivery + certificate (May 7-9 2026):**
- New landing at **`/preview/gift-landing`** (commit `8ff0e1b`, revisions `937e0f4`, `1b3d272`, `da52cbc`). Conversion-focused page aimed at gift purchasers — a different audience from the main /. Hero is a close-up of a baby's hand being held; headline "Give the baby their own .com." Form (embedded in the buy section) lets the buyer choose between "Email it now" and "Schedule the email" for recipient delivery. Page is preview-only — not promoted to `/gift` yet, no ad traffic landing on it (Dan reviews and decides when to promote).
- "Introductory Offer" labeling pushed across all pricing surfaces:
  - v1 landing: gold-pill badge added to gift card (annual intro card already had one)
  - v2 landing: annual card "Best Value" badge → "Introductory Offer"; gift card got a new "Introductory Offer" badge + highlighted styling
  - Minimal /gift form page: added INTRODUCTORY OFFER eyebrow above the price block
  - Body copy site-wide updated to say "Introductory price · …"
- **Phase 2 (commit `086f825`, May 9):** Backend now actually honors the form's two new fields.
  - DB migration `013_gift_scheduled_delivery.sql` adds 4 columns to `gift_codes`: `delivery_method`, `deliver_at`, `recipient_email_sent_at`, `certificate_token` (+ partial index for cron scan). **Migration applied to production via Supabase SQL Editor on May 9.** Backfill stamped existing purchased rows as already-sent so the cron doesn't retroactively re-spam.
  - `stripeService.createGiftCheckoutSession` accepts `deliveryMethod` + `scheduledDate`, stores in Stripe metadata. Falls back to `email_now` if scheduledDate is missing/past.
  - Webhook (gift branch in `routes/webhooks.js`) reads metadata, creates the gift via `giftService.createGiftCode`, and:
    - Always sends buyer confirmation email immediately, with a "View & Print Certificate" CTA box and timing context ("we'll send <recipient> on <date>" or "we've already sent them").
    - Sends recipient gift email inline only when `delivery_method=email_now`. For `email_scheduled`, the cron picks it up.
    - Stamps `recipient_email_sent_at` so neither path double-sends.
  - New cron `jobs/giftDeliveries.js` — runs hourly at :17, finds purchased + email_scheduled + deliver_at <= now() + not-yet-sent + has recipient_email, sends and stamps. Wired in `server.js` next to the other schedulers. **Verified running on production (`cron_runs` table shows successful run on startup).**
  - New route `GET /gift/certificate/:token` + view `marketing/gift-certificate.ejs` — public (token is the only auth, only the buyer ever sees the link). Print-optimized: gold-bordered card with brand mark, From/For names, optional message, gift code (dashed-border block), redeem URL, expiry note. `@media print` hides the toolbar and forces letter portrait. Browser "Save as PDF" works cleanly.
- **Phase 2.1 polish (commit `fa99dfe`, May 9):**
  - `/gift/success` page now shows the printable certificate inline in a gold-on-dark callout, so the buyer can print without waiting for the confirmation email. The headline subtext is now timing-aware ("we've already emailed Sam…" vs. "we'll email Sam on December 25th…").
  - Bug fix: the "webhook hasn't fired yet" race fallback in the success route was creating gift_codes without passing deliveryMethod / scheduledDate / recipientName — meaning fast-clicking buyers would silently get email_now behavior even if they'd chosen a scheduled date. Now passes everything through.
  - **`charge.refunded` webhook handler.** Stripe charge → checkout session → gift_code lookup; if the gift hasn't been redeemed yet, marks status='refunded' so the redeem flow rejects it (with a friendly "this gift has been refunded" error instead of the misleading "already redeemed"). If it HAS been redeemed, logs loudly without invalidating to avoid orphaning the recipient's account; manual handling required in that case.
  - The earlier-deferred "Refunded gift codes don't auto-invalidate" item from the monster-session open-loops list is now closed.
- **Open follow-ups for next session:**
  - Promote `/preview/gift-landing` to a real ad-landing URL (suggest `/gift-card` or replace `/gift` once Dan approves)
  - Update the gift ad campaign's destination URL once promoted
  - Consider sending the existing "purchased earlier than the migration" gift codes a printable certificate retroactively — they have `certificate_token IS NULL` and the email already went out. Low priority.

